4 HR____ RECOGNIZING MARCH 11, 2026, AS REV UP DAY OF ADVOCACY
5 IN THE STATE OF ALABAMA.
6
7 WHEREAS, there are nearly one million adults living
8 with a disability in the State of Alabama, representing a
9 significant and vital constituency with diverse
10 perspectives, needs, and contributions to our civic life;
11 and
12 WHEREAS, the right to vote and participate in the
13 democratic process is a fundamental pillar of our society,
14 yet citizens with disabilities often face unique systemic
15 barriers to registration, casting a ballot, and accessing
16 legislative information; and
17 WHEREAS, REV UP, which stands for Register, Educate,
18 Vote, Use Your Power, is a national movement focused on
19 building the power of the disability vote and protecting the
20 civil rights of Americans with disabilities; and
21 WHEREAS, the REV UP Alabama Chapter, under the
22 leadership of local advocates, works tirelessly to eliminate
23 barriers to the ballot box, aiming to ensure that every
24 Alabamian, regardless of physical, sensory, or cognitive
25 ability, has full access to his or her guaranteed rights;
26 and
27 WHEREAS, engaging in the legislative process is
28 essential for the disability community to advocate for
Page 1

essential for the disability community to advocate for
HR177 INTRODUCED
29 policies that promote independence, accessibility, and equal
30 opportunity in housing, employment, and transportation; now
31 therefore,
32 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
33 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That March 11, 2026, is hereby
34 recognized as REV UP Day of Advocacy in the State of
35 Alabama.
36 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, That this body encourages all
37 citizens to recognize the importance of the disability vote
38 and commit to working towards a more accessible and
39 inclusive democracy for all Alabamians.
